# ðŸ“˜ Week 7 â€“ Day 2: Linked List Cycle II (LeetCode 142)

## ðŸ” Problem Overview

**LeetCode 142 â€“ Linked List Cycle II**

Given the head of a linked list, return the node where the cycle begins. If there is no cycle, return `NULL`.
---

## ðŸ’¡ Key Concept

This problem is a classic application of **Floydâ€™s Cycle Detection Algorithm (Tortoise and Hare Algorithm)**.

### Why Floydâ€™s Algorithm?

* Uses **two pointers** (slow & fast)
* Works in **O(n)** time
* Uses **O(1)** extra space

---
## ðŸ’» C++ Implementation

```cpp
class Solution {
public:
    ListNode *detectCycle(ListNode *head) {
        ListNode *fast=head;
        ListNode *slow=head;
        bool iscycle=false;
        while(fast!=NULL && fast->next!=NULL) {
            slow=slow->next;
            fast=fast->next->next;
            if(slow==fast){
                iscycle=true;
                break;
            }
        }
        if(!iscycle) return NULL;
    slow=head;
    while(fast!=slow){
        slow=slow->next;
        fast=fast->next;
    }
    return slow;
    }
};
